<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,151,684]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,223,248]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[502,667,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.47" metricValueMax="1.7899999999999998" metricValueMin="1.15" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="14.7" valueMax="17.9" valueMin="11.5">11.5–17.9 mm</quantity>
; setae only black, but mixed golden and black on legs; antennomeres uniformly black, III ca. 
<number box="[439,474,260,285]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as IV, XI less than twice as long as wide; pronotum without fore transverse depression; elytral black pattern as in 
<figureCitation box="[705,786,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1396,1418]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,720,1354]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[163,1423,703,1372]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 22. Mylabris (M.) poggii Bologna: A. elytral pattern; B. mesosternum; C. male genitalia, lateral view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Bologna, 2009)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286164/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[758,786,296,320]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
A, with two series of two spots inversely oblique, and an apical narrow semilunar fascia, extended laterally on both sides and forming a subrounded extension on the inner margin; mesosternum as 
<figureCitation box="[438,521,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1396,1418]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,720,1354]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[163,1423,703,1372]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 22. Mylabris (M.) poggii Bologna: A. elytral pattern; B. mesosternum; C. male genitalia, lateral view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Bologna, 2009)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286164/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[492,521,368,392]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
B, posterior apex lighter; male gonoforceps relatively wide in lateral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1396,1418]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,720,1354]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[163,1423,703,1372]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 22. Mylabris (M.) poggii Bologna: A. elytral pattern; B. mesosternum; C. male genitalia, lateral view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Bologna, 2009)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286164/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,179,404,428]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
C); distal hook of aedeagus close to apex, and smaller than proximal one (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1088,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1396,1418]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,720,1354]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[163,1423,703,1372]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 22. Mylabris (M.) poggii Bologna: A. elytral pattern; B. mesosternum; C. male genitalia, lateral view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Bologna, 2009)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286164/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1060,1088,404,428]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,151,684]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,447,439,464]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gridelli" box="[456,627,439,464]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refString="Gridelli, E. (1930) Risultati zoologici della Missione inviata dalla R. Societa Geografica Italiana per l'esplorazione dell'oasi di Giarabub (1926 - 1927). Coleotteri. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia naturale di Genova, 54, 1 - 485." type="journal article" year="1930">
Gridelli (
<number box="[561,619,440,464]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1930.0">1930</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
was compared this species to 
<taxonomicName authority="Reiche 1866" authorityName="Reiche" authorityYear="1866" box="[981,1300,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schreibersi">
<emphasis box="[981,1144,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. schreibersi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Reiche" box="[1153,1300,439,464]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refString="Reiche, L. J. (1866) Etude sur les epeces de mylabrides de la collection de L. Reiche, suivie d'une note sur le genre Trigonurus Mulsant et description d'une espece nouvelle. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (4), 5, 627 - 642." type="journal article" year="1866">
Reiche 
<number box="[1241,1300,439,464]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1866.0">1866</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which also has a very narrow black apical border. However, the aedeagal hooks’ structure, e.g. the position of distal hooks, is similar to other Maghrebian species, specifically 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat 1840" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1840" box="[702,1001,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guerini">
<emphasis box="[702,820,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. guerini</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chevrolat" box="[827,1001,511,536]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. A. (1840) Description de Mylabrides de Barbarie. Revue Entomologique (G. Silbermann), 5 [1837], 266 - 279, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1840">
Chevrolat 
<number box="[945,1001,512,536]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1840.0">1840</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat 1840" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1840" box="[1055,1371,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricincta">
<emphasis box="[1055,1187,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. tricincta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chevrolat" box="[1194,1371,511,536]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. A. (1840) Description de Mylabrides de Barbarie. Revue Entomologique (G. Silbermann), 5 [1837], 266 - 279, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1840">
Chevrolat 
<number box="[1311,1371,512,536]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1840.0">1840</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Both these species have highly variable elytral patterns, including forms with four spots as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[1132,1241,549,572]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poggii">
<emphasis box="[1132,1241,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. poggii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with a wider black fascia at apex, gonoforceps slender and aedeagal hooks different in shape (Pardo Alcaide, 
<number box="[1261,1320,583,608]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1954.0">1954</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refString="Bologna, M. A. (1991 a) Coleoptera Meloidae. Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. Calderini, Bologna, xiv + 541 pp." type="book" year="1991" yearSuffix="a">
Bologna, 
<number box="[151,210,620,644]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1991.0">1991</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
